<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,716,992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,379,716,741]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Generic diagnosis.</emphasis>
Synapomorphic characters that define adult female 
<taxonomicName box="[1021,1178,716,740]" class="Insecta" family="Dactylopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dactylopiidae</taxonomicName>
include: presence of numerous truncate setae over dorsal surface of abdomen; quinquelocular pore clusters on a sclerotized plate each frequently associated with one or more tubular ducts.
</paragraph>
