<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,716,992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,823,848]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[358,493,824,848]" class="Insecta" family="Dactylopiidae" genus="Dactylopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[358,493,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Dactylopius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been introduced both accidentally and intentionally into many parts of the world where suitable habitat occurs (
<bibRefCitation author="Portillo" box="[495,839,860,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" refString="Portillo, L. &amp; Zimmermann, H. G. (2008) Dactylopius opuntiae: una especie en peligro de extension. pp. 69 - 73. (Eds) Llanderal, C., Zetina, D. H., Vigueras, A. L. &amp; Portillo, L. In. Grana Cochinilla y Colorantes Naturales. Colegio de Postgraduados Montecillo, Edo. de Mexico, Mexico, 124 pp." type="book chapter" year="2008">
Portillo &amp; Zimmermann 
<number box="[778,839,860,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[858,993,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Dactylopiidae" genus="Dactylopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[858,993,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Dactylopius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to arid regions of the western hemisphere where native cacti, especially opuntioid cacti, occur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
